b'UIC to lead study of negative pressure wound therapy in obese and diabetic patients'
b'UIC to lead study of negative pressure wound therapy in obese and diabetic patients'
b'With a $1.7 million, two-year grant from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, researchers in the UIC Epicenter for Prevention of Healthcare Associated Infections will determine whether negative pressure wound therapy can help reduce the incidents of surgical site infections in obese and diabetic patients.'
b'First-ever guidelines for detecting, treating perimenopausal depression'
b'First-ever guidelines for detecting, treating perimenopausal depression'
b'It is well-recognized that women are at increased risk of depression during the postpartum period when hormone levels are changing, but the risk of depression associated with perimenopause remains under-recognized and clinical recommendations on how to diagnose and treat this kind of depression in women have been lacking...until now.'
b'Tailoring behavioral therapy for depression, obesity based on how the brain responds'
b'Tailoring behavioral therapy for depression, obesity based on how the brain responds'
b'Researchers at the University of Illinois at Chicago, in collaboration with their colleagues at Stanford University and the University of Washington, will look at how an integrated behavioral therapy aimed at helping people with co-occurring obesity and depression can be adapted for individuals based on how their brain function changes in response to the intervention.'
